  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of fiduciary duty by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. As an accountant, the defendant was placed in a position of trust, which was violated to address personal financial struggles. While the financial harm to the employer is significant, several mitigating factors have been taken into consideration. The defendant has no prior criminal record, suggesting this conduct is an isolated lapse in judgment rather than a chronic pattern of criminal behavior. Additionally, the defendant has already made partial restitution, demonstrating remorse and a proactive effort to make the victim whole. Balancing the necessity to penalize the breach of trust and deter future white-collar offenses against the defendant's clean history and restitution efforts, a short period of incarceration is appropriate, which should be followed by supervised probation and a mandate to complete the repayment.",
  "verdict": 6
}
